WILDFIRE travelled in midfield between foes along the backside, took closer order shadowing the leaders three wide through the turn, bid for the lead two wide outside at the quarter pole, determinedly fought on through the lane not switching leads and gave way to the winner late who had an ideal tracking trip. ANOTHER PINKY pressed the pace on the rail in the beginning, had a narrow advantage inside at the half, set the pace while hounded outside by two rivals around the turn, was collared at the quarter pole and ran on gamely to the finish line, just faded late at the sixteenth pole to be a clear third. TACHYON SPEED stalked near the rear having one runner beaten down the backside, saved ground making little impact throughout the turn and mildly ran to the wire winning the battle for a minor role. MAGIC MODIE bobbled soon after the start trailing down the backside, caught up to rivals splitting horses two wide with five sixteenths from home. angled outside in the four path for the drive to the wire and finished with intent battling for the minor share in the end. SPEEDY ROSE assumed the lead after the start, hounded the frontrunner outside at the half, was in the mix between rivals up front in midturn, could not match strides with the leading pair in upper stretch and faltered on the fence the final sixteenth. DADDY'S DAISY settled on the the outside three deep in mid-pack down the backside, could not quicken running outside of other horses around the bend and came up empty in the stretch drive.

NIGHT STRIKER improved position down the backstretch on the fence, continued on gaining on the fence on horses throughout the turn, chased the long gone winner in vain down the stretch and just held on saving the place share at the wire. SUGAR IT'S ELI was situated in midfield two wide between foes at the half, began to pick up horses three wide at the quarter pole and closed belatedly down the lane just missing second place in a tight photo at the wire. SPIRIT OF SEATTLE settled three wide outside foes in midfield at the half, kept pace with runners three wide outside horse on the turn and finished up willingly to the wire passing runners. GLORIOUS REVENGE was brushed inside at the break, chased the winner down the backside and through the turn, dueled between foes in the four path for the minors in upper stretch and tired with a furlong left to run. BLONDINA'S BOY had a poor start to trail down the backside, could still see the field running around the bend and showed good late energy passing some weary runners down the stretch. SQUEEZETHESHARMAN broke out at the start, tracked the front two at the half, closed in to battle four wide at the top of the lane for the runners up share, could not go on and yielded in the five path in mid-stretch. WETIKO had one runner beaten in the early going, made a brief rally three wide at the three furlong marker outside rivals and could not get involved running on the wrong lead through the stretch. QURBAAN'S KINGDOM was shuffled back soon after the start to stalk near the rear down the backside, made little impression running around the oval and was no menace in the stretch drive. DRILLHALL veered in sharply at the start, stalked near the rear down the backside, offered little run throughout the turn and emptied out turning for home.
